pr_review_body:
@NicolasHug Thanks, the changes look good.

How would you feel about adding in the metrics of each weights a single `epe` field that stores the value of the "most appropriate" experiment. Note that this idea implicitly exists already in all other models. For example the `acc@1` usually reports the value on the validation set used for training; there are others we could be reporting (or example ImageNet Real/V2 for classification) but currently dont. This way you can have a single metric that summarizes the model metrics and move the per-dataset breakdown on a separate list. I've provided some examples of this previously at https://github.com/pytorch/vision/pull/5859#discussion_r856143326

We don't have to solve this now but we need to fix this before the release to avoid BC breakages on the future.

@nabokovas Thank you very much for this update! You've just done my job 🙂 

@jameslamb Let me kindly disagree with you. According to our policy, we try to use the most recent environments at Travis (https://github.com/microsoft/LightGBM/pull/3393#issue-486186591) and update them quite often.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25141164/97639748-3d1dc880-1a50-11eb-8fd4-ec207de3df4c.png)


I believe it's better to spot a compilation problem at our CI before users come and report it.
Moreover, we are speaking about macOS where it seems users tend to use the last available software in contrast to Linux where one have to use 10-years old CentOS distribution.

FYI, yesterday I tried to use Big Sur, but unfortunately without any luck due to dependency unavailability: #3499.

Sorry for the last minute changes (that happens, when you have to use a phone for code review...)

The code looks good. Thank you for that new instrument (and small typo fix). 

@bilderbuchi and @msmttchr can this be merged? 

@tomverbeure are you finished with the instrument (after the two changes), such that it may be merged after the two changes?

@bnmajor thank you! 

Could we also please add a test notebook?

Perhaps an example from the master branch or an adaptation of https://examples.itk.org/src/core/transform/deformavolumewithathinplatespline/documentation?highlight=plate ?
